events.description: Byzantine Emperor Justin I names his nephew Justinian I as co-ruler and successor to the throne.
events.html: • 527 – Byzantine Emperor Justin I names his nephew Justinian I as co-ruler and successor to the throne.[1]

events.description: Alexios I Komnenos overthrows the Byzantine emperor Nikephoros III Botaneiates, and, after his troops spend three days extensively looting Constantinople, is formally crowned on April 4.
events.html: • 1081 – Alexios I Komnenos overthrows the Byzantine emperor Nikephoros III Botaneiates,[2] and, after his troops spend three days extensively looting Constantinople, is formally crowned on April 4.[3]

events.description: In the Eighty Years' War, the Watergeuzen capture Brielle from the Seventeen Provinces, gaining the first foothold on land for what would become the Dutch Republic.
events.html: • 1572 – In the Eighty Years' War, the Watergeuzen capture Brielle from the Seventeen Provinces, gaining the first foothold on land for what would become the Dutch Republic.[4]

events.description: In New York City, the United States House of Representatives achieves its first quorum and elects Frederick Muhlenberg of Pennsylvania as its first Speaker.
events.html: • 1789 – In New York City, the United States House of Representatives achieves its first quorum and elects Frederick Muhlenberg of Pennsylvania as its first Speaker.[5]

entities.name: Speaker of the United States House of Representatives

events.description: The Convention of 1833, a political gathering of settlers in Mexican Texas to help draft a series of petitions to the Mexican government, begins in San Felipe de Austin.
events.html: • 1833 – The Convention of 1833, a political gathering of settlers in Mexican Texas to help draft a series of petitions to the Mexican government, begins in San Felipe de Austin.[6]

events.description: American Civil War: Union troops led by Philip Sheridan decisively defeat Confederate troops led by George Pickett, cutting the Army of Northern Virginia's last supply line during the Siege of Petersburg.
events.html: • 1865 – American Civil War: Union troops led by Philip Sheridan decisively defeat Confederate troops led by George Pickett, cutting the Army of Northern Virginia's last supply line during the Siege of Petersburg.[7]

events.description: Singapore becomes a British crown colony.
events.html: • 1867 – Singapore becomes a British crown colony.[8]

events.description: The White Star steamer SS Atlantic sinks off Nova Scotia, killing 547 in one of the worst marine disasters of the 19th century.
events.html: • 1873 – The White Star steamer SS Atlantic sinks off Nova Scotia, killing 547 in one of the worst marine disasters of the 19th century.[9]

events.description: Prince George becomes absolute monarch of the Cretan State.
events.html: • 1900 – Prince George becomes absolute monarch of the Cretan State.[10]

entities.name: Prince George of Greece and Denmark

events.description: The Territorial Force (renamed Territorial Army in 1920) is formed as a volunteer reserve component of the British Army.
events.html: • 1908 – The Territorial Force (renamed Territorial Army in 1920) is formed as a volunteer reserve component of the British Army.[11]

events.description: The Royal Air Force is created by the merger of the Royal Flying Corps and the Royal Naval Air Service.
events.html: • 1918 – The Royal Air Force is created by the merger of the Royal Flying Corps and the Royal Naval Air Service.[12]

events.description: In newly formed Northern Ireland, six Catholics are murdered in the Arnon Street killings, one week after six others were killed in the  McMahon killings.
events.html: • 1922 – In newly formed Northern Ireland, six Catholics are murdered in the Arnon Street killings, one week after six others were killed in the McMahon killings.[13]

events.description: Adolf Hitler is sentenced to five years imprisonment for his participation in the "Beer Hall Putsch" but spends only nine months in jail.
events.html: • 1924 – Adolf Hitler is sentenced to five years imprisonment for his participation in the "Beer Hall Putsch" but spends only nine months in jail.[14]

events.description: The Royal Canadian Air Force is formed.
events.html: • 1924 – The Royal Canadian Air Force is formed.[15]

events.description: The recently elected Nazis under Julius Streicher organize a one-day boycott of all Jewish-owned businesses in Germany, ushering in a series of anti-Semitic acts.
events.html: • 1933 – The recently elected Nazis under Julius Streicher organize a one-day boycott of all Jewish-owned businesses in Germany, ushering in a series of anti-Semitic acts.[16]

events.description: India's central banking institution, the Reserve Bank of India, is formed.
events.html: • 1935 – India's central banking institution, the Reserve Bank of India, is formed.[17]

events.description: Aden becomes a British crown colony.
events.html: • 1937 – Aden becomes a British crown colony.

events.description: The Royal New Zealand Air Force is formed as an independent service.
events.html: • 1937 – The Royal New Zealand Air Force is formed as an independent service.[18]

events.description: Spanish Civil War: Generalísimo Francisco Franco of the Spanish State announces the end of the Spanish Civil War, when the last of the Republican forces surrender.
events.html: • 1939 – Spanish Civil War: Generalísimo Francisco Franco of the Spanish State announces the end of the Spanish Civil War, when the last of the Republican forces surrender.[19]

events.description: Fântâna Albă massacre: Between two hundred and two thousand Romanian civilians are killed by Soviet Border Troops.
events.html: • 1941 – Fântâna Albă massacre: Between two hundred and two thousand Romanian civilians are killed by Soviet Border Troops.[20]

events.description: A military coup in Iraq overthrows the regime of 'Abd al-Ilah and installs Rashid Ali al-Gaylani as Prime Minister.
events.html: • 1941 – A military coup in Iraq overthrows the regime of 'Abd al-Ilah and installs Rashid Ali al-Gaylani as Prime Minister.[21]

events.description: World War II: Navigation errors lead to an accidental American bombing of the Swiss city of Schaffhausen.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: Navigation errors lead to an accidental American bombing of the Swiss city of Schaffhausen.[22]

entities.name: Aerial incidents in Switzerland in World War II

events.description: World War II: The Tenth United States Army attacks the Thirty-Second Japanese Army on Okinawa.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: The Tenth United States Army attacks the Thirty-Second Japanese Army on Okinawa.[23]

events.description: The 8.6 Mw  Aleutian Islands earthquake shakes the Aleutian Islands with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VI (Strong). A destructive tsunami reaches the Hawaiian Islands resulting in dozens of deaths, mostly in Hilo, Hawaii.
events.html: • 1946 – The 8.6 Mw  Aleutian Islands earthquake shakes the Aleutian Islands with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VI (Strong). A destructive tsunami reaches the Hawaiian Islands resulting in dozens of deaths, mostly in Hilo, Hawaii.[24]

events.description: The Malayan Union is established. Protests from locals led to the establishment of the Federation of Malaya two years later.
events.html: • 1946 – The Malayan Union is established. Protests from locals led to the establishment of the Federation of Malaya two years later.[25]

events.description: The only mutiny in the history of the Royal New Zealand Navy begins.
events.html: • 1947 – The only mutiny in the history of the Royal New Zealand Navy begins.[26]

events.description: Cold War: Communist forces respond to the introduction of the Deutsche Mark by attempting to force the western powers to withdraw from Berlin.
events.html: • 1948 – Cold War: Communist forces respond to the introduction of the Deutsche Mark by attempting to force the western powers to withdraw from Berlin.[27]

events.description: Faroe Islands gain autonomy from Denmark.
events.html: • 1948 – Faroe Islands gain autonomy from Denmark.[28]

events.description: Chinese Civil War: The Chinese Communist Party holds unsuccessful peace talks with the Nationalist Party in Beijing, after three years of fighting.
events.html: • 1949 – Chinese Civil War: The Chinese Communist Party holds unsuccessful peace talks with the Nationalist Party in Beijing, after three years of fighting.

events.description: The Government of Canada repeals Japanese-Canadian internment after seven years.
events.html: • 1949 – The Government of Canada repeals Japanese-Canadian internment after seven years.[29]

events.description: United States President Dwight D. Eisenhower authorizes the creation of the United States Air Force Academy in Colorado Springs, Colorado.
events.html: • 1954 – United States President Dwight D. Eisenhower authorizes the creation of the United States Air Force Academy in Colorado Springs, Colorado.[30]

events.description: The EOKA rebellion against the British Empire begins in Cyprus, with the goal of unifying with Greece.
events.html: • 1955 – The EOKA rebellion against the British Empire begins in Cyprus, with the goal of unifying with Greece.[31]

events.description: The TIROS-1 satellite transmits the first television picture from space.
events.html: • 1960 – The TIROS-1 satellite transmits the first television picture from space.[32]

events.description: The British Admiralty, War Office and Air Ministry are replaced by a unified Defence Council of the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1964 – The British Admiralty, War Office and Air Ministry are replaced by a unified Defence Council of the United Kingdom.[33]

entities.name: Defence Council of the United Kingdom

events.description: The Hawker Siddeley Harrier, the first operational fighter aircraft with Vertical/Short Takeoff and Landing capabilities, enters service with the Royal Air Force.
events.html: • 1969 – The Hawker Siddeley Harrier, the first operational fighter aircraft with Vertical/Short Takeoff and Landing capabilities, enters service with the Royal Air Force.[34]

events.description: President Richard Nixon signs the Public Health Cigarette Smoking Act into law.
events.html: • 1970 – President Richard Nixon signs the Public Health Cigarette Smoking Act into law.[35]

events.description: A Royal Air Maroc Sud Aviation Caravelle crashes near Berrechid, Morocco, killing 61.
events.html: • 1970 – A Royal Air Maroc Sud Aviation Caravelle crashes near Berrechid, Morocco, killing 61.[36]

entities.name: 1970 Berrechid Royal Air Maroc Caravelle crash

events.description: Bangladesh Liberation War: The Pakistan Army massacre more than a thousand people in Keraniganj Upazila, Bangladesh.
events.html: • 1971 – Bangladesh Liberation War: The Pakistan Army massacre more than a thousand people in Keraniganj Upazila, Bangladesh.

events.description: Project Tiger, a tiger conservation project, is launched in the Jim Corbett National Park, India.
events.html: • 1973 – Project Tiger, a tiger conservation project, is launched in the Jim Corbett National Park, India.

events.description: The Local Government Act 1972 of England and Wales comes into effect.
events.html: • 1974 – The Local Government Act 1972 of England and Wales comes into effect.[37]

events.description: Steve Jobs and Steve Wozniak found Apple Computer, Inc.
events.html: • 1976 – Steve Jobs and Steve Wozniak found Apple Computer, Inc.[38]

events.description: Iran becomes an Islamic republic by a 99% vote, officially overthrowing the Shah.
events.html: • 1979 – Iran becomes an Islamic republic by a 99% vote, officially overthrowing the Shah.[39]

events.description: Singer Marvin Gaye is shot to death by his father in his home in Arlington Heights, Los Angeles, California.
events.html: • 1984 – Singer Marvin Gaye is shot to death by his father in his home in Arlington Heights, Los Angeles, California.[40]

events.description: Communist Party of Nepal (Mashal) cadres attack a number of police stations in Kathmandu, seeking to incite a popular rebellion.
events.html: • 1986 – Communist Party of Nepal (Mashal) cadres attack a number of police stations in Kathmandu, seeking to incite a popular rebellion.[41]

events.description: Margaret Thatcher's new local government tax, the Community Charge (commonly known as the "poll tax"), is introduced in Scotland.
events.html: • 1989 – Margaret Thatcher's new local government tax, the Community Charge (commonly known as the "poll tax"), is introduced in Scotland.[42]

events.description: NASCAR racer Alan Kulwicki is killed in a plane crash near the Tri-Cities Regional Airport in Blountville, Tennessee.
events.html: • 1993 – NASCAR racer Alan Kulwicki is killed in a plane crash near the Tri-Cities Regional Airport in Blountville, Tennessee.[43]

events.description: Comet Hale–Bopp is seen passing at perihelion.
events.html: • 1997 – Comet Hale–Bopp is seen passing at perihelion.[44]

events.description: Nunavut is established as a Canadian territory carved out of the eastern part of the Northwest Territories.
events.html: • 1999 – Nunavut is established as a Canadian territory carved out of the eastern part of the Northwest Territories.[45]

events.description: An EP-3E United States Navy surveillance aircraft collides with a Chinese People's Liberation Army Shenyang J-8 fighter jet. The Chinese pilot ejected but is subsequently lost. The Navy crew makes an emergency landing in Hainan, China and is detained.
events.html: • 2001 – An EP-3E United States Navy surveillance aircraft collides with a Chinese People's Liberation Army Shenyang J-8 fighter jet. The Chinese pilot ejected but is subsequently lost. The Navy crew makes an emergency landing in Hainan, China and is detained.[46]

events.description: Former President of Federal Republic of Yugoslavia Slobodan Milošević surrenders to police special forces, to be tried on war crimes charges.
events.html: • 2001 – Former President of Federal Republic of Yugoslavia Slobodan Milošević surrenders to police special forces, to be tried on war crimes charges.[47]

events.description: Same-sex marriage becomes legal in the Netherlands, the first contemporary country to allow it.
events.html: • 2001 – Same-sex marriage becomes legal in the Netherlands, the first contemporary country to allow it.[48]

events.description: Google launches its Email service Gmail.
events.html: • 2004 – Google launches its Email service Gmail.[49]

events.description: Serious Organised Crime Agency (SOCA) of the Government of the United Kingdom is enforced, but later merged into National Crime Agency on 7 October 2013.
events.html: • 2006 – Serious Organised Crime Agency (SOCA) of the Government of the United Kingdom is enforced, but later merged into National Crime Agency on 7 October 2013.

events.description: After protests against the burning of the Quran turn violent, a mob attacks a United Nations compound in Mazar-i-Sharif, Afghanistan, resulting in the deaths of fourteen people, including seven UN workers.
events.html: • 2011 – After protests against the burning of the Quran turn violent, a mob attacks a United Nations compound in Mazar-i-Sharif, Afghanistan, resulting in the deaths of fourteen people, including seven UN workers.[50]
